# Jquery Mobile site for UNC Cause 2011

## Requirements

 - Rubygems version > 1.7.7
 - Install the [jekyll](https://github.com/mojombo/jekyll) gem
 - npm
 - [Coffee Script](http://jashkenas.github.com/coffee-script/)
 
## Building an instance

   $ cd ~/projects/dev/cause-mobile
   $ jekyll
   $ coffee --compile js/app.coffee

This should build an instance of the site in the `_site` folder. 

## Running the development server

   $ cd ~/projects/dev/cause-mobile
   $ jekyll --serve --auto
   $ coffee --watch --compile js/app.coffee

Now if you point your browser to [http://localhost:4000](http://localhost:4000)
you should get an instance of the site in your browser.

